olive oil
2 potato
1 packet chicken breast
1 sachet Classic Roast Seasoning
1 carrot
1 packet Shredded Cabbage Mix
drizzle white wine vinegar
1 packet Red Wine Jus
2 Burger Bun
1 packet mayonnaise
1 packet Shredded Cheddar Cheese

• Preheat oven to 220°C/200°C fan-forced. Cut potato into 0.5cm-thick rounds, then place on a lined oven tray.
• Add a drizzle of olive oil and a pinch of salt and pepper. Toss to coat, spread out evenly, then roast until golden, 20-25 minutes.
• In last 5 minutes of cook time, remove potato from oven, sprinkle with shredded Cheddar and bake until golden and crisp, 5 minutes.

Little cooks: Help toss the potatoes!

• Meanwhile, boil the kettle. Place your hand flat on top of chicken breastand slice through horizontally to make two thin steaks.
• In a medium bowl, combine chicken, garlic & herb seasoning and a drizzle of olive oil.
• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over medium-high heat.
• Cook chicken until cooked through, 3-5 minutes each side (cook in batches if your pan is getting crowded).

TIP: Chicken is cooked through when it's no longer pink inside.

• Meanwhile, grate carrot.
• In a second medium bowl, combine shredded red cabbage, carrot and a drizzle of white wine vinegar and olive oil. Season and set aside.
• In a small heatproof bowl, combine gravy granules and the boiling water (1/2 cup for 2 people / 1 cup for 4 people), whisking, until smooth, 1 minute.
• Halve burger buns and bake directly on a wire oven rack until heated through, 2-3 minutes.

• Spread each bun with mayonnaise, top with some roasted potatoes, slaw, and chicken.
• Serve with remaining potatoes, slaw and gravy. Enjoy!

Little cooks: Take the lead and help build the burgers!